WEBVTT

00:02.160 --> 00:03.730
NARRATOR:
Previously on The Vampire Diaries:

00:03.880 --> 00:05.320
ELENA: I'm Elena.
STEFAN: I'm Stefan.

00:05.480 --> 00:06.811
<i>Love brought me to Mystic Falls.</i>

00:07.560 --> 00:09.369
<i>Love drove me away.</i>

00:09.520 --> 00:12.490
I am not sorry that I'm in love with you,
Damon.

00:12.640 --> 00:14.608
<i>STEFAN:
We've all made sacrifices.</i>

00:15.840 --> 00:17.842
[SPEAKS IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE
THEN GASPS]

00:18.040 --> 00:19.565
I did a spell that brought you back.

00:19.720 --> 00:22.087
- You can see ghosts, we can talk.
- No, you can't be dead.

00:22.560 --> 00:23.846
[GRUNTING]

00:27.760 --> 00:29.888
Have a nice human life, Katherine.

00:30.040 --> 00:31.485
<i>STEFAN:
But our greatest threat is still out there.</i>

00:31.640 --> 00:34.120
- Silas.
- Hello, my shadow self.

00:34.280 --> 00:35.361
[GRUNTS]

00:36.760 --> 00:41.129
<i>STEFAN: And he looks just like me.</i>
- Aah!

00:45.640 --> 00:47.722
ELENA:
Hey, Bonnie.

00:47.880 --> 00:53.171
<i>How is the summer almost over
and yet I feel like I got nothing done?</i>

00:53.360 --> 00:54.885
[ELENA LAUGHING]

00:57.000 --> 00:59.685
<i>Sounds like you're having fun
traveling with your mom.</i>

00:59.880 --> 01:03.726
<i>I still don't know how I'm supposed
to do this whole college thing without you.</i>

01:03.880 --> 01:07.930
<i>Caroline agrees. She spent the summer
designing the color palette for our dorm...</i>

01:08.080 --> 01:12.005
<i>while Tyler's been away
helping some wolf pack in Tennessee.</i>

01:12.160 --> 01:14.845
Don't worry, I already sent them
your application, Tyler.

01:15.000 --> 01:19.642
All you have to do is register for classes
and show up.

01:23.280 --> 01:26.762
ELENA: <i>Matt and Rebekah
have been sending postcards.</i>

01:26.920 --> 01:30.003
<i>I think that they're in Amsterdam now.
Or was it Prague?</i>

01:30.520 --> 01:35.686
<i>I can't keep track. And honestly,
I'm not sure I really want to.</i>

01:39.800 --> 01:41.370
[SPEAKS IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

01:47.120 --> 01:49.805
<i>Anyway, I can't wait to see you.</i>

01:50.280 --> 01:51.441
<i>When do you get back?</i>

01:51.720 --> 01:53.404
<i>Love, Elena.</i>

01:54.720 --> 01:56.210
JEREMY:
Dear Elena.

01:56.360 --> 01:58.806
Wait, don't start with "dear"

01:59.280 --> 02:01.851
Bad enough you're dead,
now you're a control freak?

02:02.000 --> 02:04.367
I'm just saying,
people don't say "dear" anymore.

02:04.560 --> 02:08.485
Fine. How about,
"Hey, Elena. What's up?"

02:09.600 --> 02:11.284
Thank you.

02:12.160 --> 02:14.606
<i>BONNIE:
Hey, Elena. What's up?</i>

02:14.760 --> 02:18.685
<i>You guys have no idea
how much I miss you.</i>

02:18.840 --> 02:22.322
<i>I've been e-mailing with Jeremy,
he says it's been surreal to be alive.</i>

02:24.440 --> 02:27.284
Hey, um, sor... I thought you left.

02:27.440 --> 02:29.442
I did.

02:29.600 --> 02:33.685
- Uh, five hours ago.
- All right, well, there's, uh, pizza in the frid...

02:34.160 --> 02:36.242
[ELENA CHUCKLES]

02:36.400 --> 02:38.971
BONNIE: <i>If Katherine ingesting
the only cure on this Earth...</i>

02:39.120 --> 02:41.122
<i>and having to live as a human
isn't justice...</i>

02:41.280 --> 02:43.169
[WOMAN CHEERING]

02:44.400 --> 02:46.129
<i>I don't know what is.</i>

02:50.200 --> 02:54.603
<i>I miss you guys.
I'm glad you're having a great summer.</i>

02:54.840 --> 02:57.844
<i>PS, have you heard from Stefan?</i>

03:04.280 --> 03:06.089
You Okay?

03:06.240 --> 03:10.768
Yeah, I've just got this weird feeling
like something bad's about to happen.

03:11.440 --> 03:13.727
Well, it is. You're leaving tomorrow.

03:14.440 --> 03:18.570
You're trading all this
for communal showers and a meal plan.

03:18.760 --> 03:21.730
Can't you just be a normal boyfriend
and support me...

03:21.880 --> 03:24.645
as I attempt to have
a normal college experience?

03:24.880 --> 03:29.090
I'd rather ply you with champagne
and spend the night convincing you to stay.

03:29.240 --> 03:30.651
[CHUCKLES]

03:44.320 --> 03:46.288
[SIGHS]

03:57.240 --> 03:58.969
[SIGHS]

04:21.800 --> 04:23.245
JEREMY:
<i>There</i> were issues at home.

04:23.600 --> 04:27.047
Ever since I lost my parents and my aunt,
I've been acting out.

04:27.240 --> 04:28.924
Drugs. Drinking.

04:29.120 --> 04:36.129
I was looking for attention, so I lit my
house on fire and faked my own death.

04:36.360 --> 04:40.001
Really stress the drug thing. And I'd
definitely say the fire was an accident...

04:40.160 --> 04:45.769
because there's crazy
and then there's, well, me.

04:45.920 --> 04:48.924
Or I could not go back, considering
my school already had a memorial for me.

04:49.080 --> 04:50.127
[CAR HORN HONKS NEARBY]

04:50.280 --> 04:52.521
DAMON: Caroline just pulled up.
ELENA: I can't leave.

04:52.720 --> 04:56.088
I should stay and at least wait
until Jeremy settles into school.

04:56.240 --> 04:58.163
DAMON:
You're leaving. You're going to college.

04:58.320 --> 05:01.483
You're gonna drink cheap beer
and protest things you don't care about.

05:01.640 --> 05:05.690
And I am going to take care
of your little brother. Trust me.

05:06.960 --> 05:09.201
You have nothing to worry about.

05:10.600 --> 05:13.171
Okay, at least Whitmore's
only a few hours away.

05:13.320 --> 05:15.448
So if there's anything you need,
just call me.

05:15.600 --> 05:18.206
Hey. See you on laundry day.

05:23.840 --> 05:25.569
- Heh.
ELENA: Bye.

05:27.280 --> 05:31.808
So how do you think this whole
long-distance thing is gonna work?

05:31.960 --> 05:35.282
Well, I personally plan on forgetting about
you the second you walk out the door.

05:35.480 --> 05:36.925
[CHUCKLES]

05:46.520 --> 05:50.161
- I love you.
- I love you.

05:53.520 --> 05:55.409
All right.

05:57.240 --> 05:58.810
Off you go.

06:15.400 --> 06:17.926
Yeah, no, we're not doing this.

06:18.200 --> 06:19.884
Go to school.

06:27.160 --> 06:28.924
CAROLINE:
You're dreaming about Stefan?

06:29.080 --> 06:32.721
They're not dreams, it's more of a feeling.
Maybe I should call him.

06:32.880 --> 06:36.407
So he can hear how happy you are
with Damon? Absolutely not.

06:36.560 --> 06:38.164
He'll call you when he's ready.

06:38.320 --> 06:41.847
So I should just live
with this nagging pit in my stomach?

06:42.040 --> 06:44.964
Okay, Elena, that pit is called guilt.

06:45.120 --> 06:48.522
You feel terrible because you broke
Stefan's heart. That nagging feeling...

06:48.680 --> 06:52.480
is your brain waking up to tell you
that you've made a horrible...

06:52.680 --> 06:54.762
yet completely reversible mistake.

06:54.920 --> 06:58.561
Nice try. Besides,
Stefan and I left things in a good place.

06:58.720 --> 07:02.645
Doesn't mean he hasn't been thinking
about you shacking up with his brother.

07:02.800 --> 07:05.565
Hello. Mom ears. Still here.

07:06.720 --> 07:08.370
[CHUCKLES]

07:10.680 --> 07:14.048
We're in college, Caroline.

07:14.320 --> 07:18.166
We actually made it. We're here.

07:18.320 --> 07:20.482
We're all here together.

07:30.360 --> 07:32.761
You brought a Panini press?

07:32.920 --> 07:37.482
- Small appliances by the fridge.
- Okay, that's the last one.

07:38.320 --> 07:39.890
All right, give me a goodbye hug...

07:40.040 --> 07:42.964
before I change my mind
and drag you home with me.

07:43.440 --> 07:46.808
Oh. You can call as much as you want,
you know?

07:46.960 --> 07:49.645
Mom, we'll be fine.

07:51.360 --> 07:52.930
Come here.

07:55.640 --> 07:58.689
This is where your dad
fell in love with medicine, you know?

07:59.400 --> 08:02.688
He would be really proud to see you here.

08:03.520 --> 08:05.010
Thank you.

08:10.280 --> 08:13.966
Go. Before I change my mind
and make you stay.

08:14.120 --> 08:16.521
I'm going, I'm going. I love you.

08:17.720 --> 08:19.051
Bye, girls.

08:22.560 --> 08:25.166
So, roomie,
I think we should drink to something.

08:25.320 --> 08:27.800
I couldn't agree more, roomie.

08:27.960 --> 08:29.450
[ELENA CHUCKLES]

08:31.960 --> 08:35.248
To us, and college,
and being functional vampires.

08:35.400 --> 08:37.640
To the next chapter in our lives.

08:37.799 --> 08:39.450
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

08:43.000 --> 08:46.083
- Hi.
- Uh, who are you?

08:46.240 --> 08:48.049
I'm Megan. Your roommate.

08:52.080 --> 08:55.721
Caroline says, "Get your ass to Whitmore,
Bonnie. We need you."

08:56.800 --> 08:59.485
Just tell her I'm at the Grand Canyon.

08:59.680 --> 09:02.206
You realize you're postponing
the inevitable, right?

09:02.360 --> 09:05.204
What happens when your dad finds out
you've been dead?

09:05.360 --> 09:09.081
How many postcards have I sent him?
How many times has he called?

09:09.240 --> 09:11.641
I've done enough.
He's clearly not missing me.

09:11.800 --> 09:14.451
- What about Elena?
- I just saw her at college.

09:14.600 --> 09:16.807
She seemed genuinely happy.

09:16.960 --> 09:19.042
I am not taking that away from her.

09:23.120 --> 09:25.487
We're lucky, Jer.

09:26.200 --> 09:29.409
How many people die and still get
to talk to their best friends?

09:30.480 --> 09:33.689
How many best friends
can't feel each other?

09:38.000 --> 09:43.040
I should get going. The freak who faked
his own death can't also be late for math.

09:43.200 --> 09:44.770
[STUDENTS CHATTERING]

09:51.280 --> 09:53.806
DAMON [OVER <i>PHONE]:
What? Wait</i> a <i>minute, how'd that happen?</i>

09:53.960 --> 09:56.611
There must have been a mix-up
at the housing office.

09:56.760 --> 10:00.003
<i>DAMON:. Compulsion. it's the ultimate
unwanted-roommate repellent.</i>

10:00.200 --> 10:02.487
That's exactly what Caroline said.

10:02.640 --> 10:04.608
Right. Then compel her ass out the door.

10:04.760 --> 10:09.448
Damon, what's the point in going to college
if we recreate what happens in Mystic Falls?

10:09.600 --> 10:12.251
Look at you, giving it the old college try.

10:12.400 --> 10:15.370
- Did Jeremy get to school okay?
- Yup. Showered. Groomed.

10:15.520 --> 10:18.046
Even cut the crusts
off of his PB&J myself.

10:18.200 --> 10:21.010
So, what you're saying is that
me being here...

10:21.160 --> 10:24.482
<i>and you being there,
this could actually work?</i>

10:28.400 --> 10:30.050
Exactly. Heh.

10:30.200 --> 10:34.046
Listen, I gotta, uh, go.

10:35.560 --> 10:38.564
It's been a long summer, Damon.

10:39.360 --> 10:40.885
Katherine.

10:44.920 --> 10:46.729
[CHATTERING]

11:01.720 --> 11:04.963
Five-star restaurants in Paris
to tapping kegs in a park.

11:06.400 --> 11:07.640
Tragic.

11:13.200 --> 11:16.647
- I thought we said no strings.
- Who said there were strings?

11:18.400 --> 11:19.640
Weren't you leaving town?

11:19.800 --> 11:23.168
I thought I'd give you one last chance
to come with me.

11:23.680 --> 11:26.763
I have to work. I'm in the real world now.
I need a paycheck.

11:26.920 --> 11:30.481
Great. Maybe you could replace those
earrings that Nadia stole in Prague.

11:30.640 --> 11:32.449
Those earrings don't bring you
back to life.

11:32.600 --> 11:35.604
How am I gonna explain to Jeremy
that she stole his Gilbert ring?

11:35.760 --> 11:37.683
Tell him you had a threesome.
He'll understand.

11:38.320 --> 11:41.051
Don't call. Don't write.

11:41.200 --> 11:42.611
And whatever you do...

11:43.480 --> 11:45.801
don't you dare miss me.

12:04.200 --> 12:06.328
Hey. Look who's back.

12:06.480 --> 12:09.211
- Look who's, uh, eating her feelings.
- Yeah.

12:09.360 --> 12:11.601
- I just dropped the girls off at Whitmore.
- Ah.

12:11.760 --> 12:14.445
Join me as I drown my sorrow
in comfort food.

12:20.600 --> 12:24.047
- What are you doing?
- I'm outing myself as not-Stefan.

12:24.600 --> 12:28.161
Obviously. Don't be afraid. Don't move.

12:31.720 --> 12:33.085
What's happening?

12:33.240 --> 12:34.765
We've met before, actually.

12:34.920 --> 12:38.481
When I was appearing as your daughter?
I bashed your head in?

12:38.640 --> 12:41.211
- Does that ring any bells?
- Silas.

12:41.400 --> 12:42.561
Indeed.

12:42.720 --> 12:47.362
I am a 2000-year-old immortal that Caroline
and her friends thought they got rid of.

12:47.520 --> 12:49.443
Are you appearing to me as Stefan?

12:49.600 --> 12:54.891
Well, yes and no. This is my true form.
Stefan is my doppelganger.

12:57.240 --> 13:00.562
You're confused. I know that
because I can read your thoughts.

13:00.720 --> 13:03.803
It's understandable.
I've been a little cryptic lately.

13:03.960 --> 13:05.564
What's with the knife?

13:05.760 --> 13:07.967
- Most vampires go straight for the neck.
- Ugh.

13:08.120 --> 13:10.361
Please, Liz. I came first.

13:10.520 --> 13:14.081
Vampires are nothing more than
a disgusting perversion of me.

13:14.240 --> 13:16.208
I'm unkillable, I'm immortal and psychic.

13:16.360 --> 13:18.328
And to function, I need human blood.

13:18.520 --> 13:22.161
But don't ever call me a vampire.

13:28.160 --> 13:29.491
Cheers.

13:31.800 --> 13:33.245
Ah.

13:37.840 --> 13:42.050
Unfortunately, I can see that you
can't help me find what I'm looking for.

13:42.200 --> 13:46.250
So all you need to remember, Liz...

13:47.000 --> 13:51.403
is that Stefan stopped by to say hello.

13:56.560 --> 14:00.167
Call your friends, Stefan.
Let them know you're okay?

14:02.520 --> 14:03.851
Will do, sheriff.

14:07.360 --> 14:09.727
- So your current boyfriend Damien...
- Damon.

14:09.880 --> 14:11.644
- Is your ex's brother.
- Stefan.

14:11.800 --> 14:15.122
And you and Stefan are friends,
but he left without saying goodbye?

14:15.280 --> 14:18.011
- Do you think that I should call him?
MEGAN & CAROLINE: No way.

14:18.680 --> 14:21.763
- Do you have a boyfriend, Caroline?
- I do. His name's Tyler.

14:21.960 --> 14:25.009
He had to miss move-in day
but he'll be here for classes.

14:25.160 --> 14:28.209
Assuming he registers.
And picks a dorm. And buys books.

14:28.360 --> 14:32.365
Speaking of minding one's own business,
let's talk roommate ground rules.

14:32.520 --> 14:35.046
- Privacy is very important to me.
- Same here.

14:35.200 --> 14:38.886
I have low blood sugar. My diet's finicky,
so keep your paws off my stuff.

14:39.040 --> 14:41.805
- We'll split up shelves.
- If I suddenly get up to leave...

14:41.960 --> 14:45.567
or disappear for a while,
don't follow me or look for me.

14:46.200 --> 14:49.329
- Okay. Sounds good.
ELENA: Heh.

14:49.480 --> 14:52.165
- Great. Then we agree on everything.
JESSE: Excuse me, ladies.

14:52.840 --> 14:54.968
Party at Whitmore House tonight.

14:58.840 --> 14:59.887
We'll be there.

15:01.560 --> 15:02.971
I hope so.

15:07.160 --> 15:08.685
[CHUCKLING]

15:09.200 --> 15:11.123
I love college.

15:12.880 --> 15:14.370
[CELL PHONE BUZZING]

15:17.920 --> 15:19.081
[SIGHS]

15:21.640 --> 15:23.290
Look who rose from the dead.

15:29.560 --> 15:32.484
Nice phone. Does it ever ring?

15:33.840 --> 15:34.887
[GRUNTING]

15:38.200 --> 15:39.725
[STUDENTS GASPING]

15:39.880 --> 15:41.245
GIRL:
What is he doing?

15:41.400 --> 15:43.004
[STUDENTS CHATTERING]

15:55.960 --> 15:58.167
You're gonna have to cut me off soon.

15:58.320 --> 16:01.688
My tolerance is a joke now.

16:01.840 --> 16:04.446
It's just so glorious.

16:04.920 --> 16:07.730
- You're miserable.
- Please.

16:07.880 --> 16:10.770
I'm Katherine Pierce. I'm a survivor.

16:10.920 --> 16:13.924
You're a liar. Your hair's messed up.
Your nails are chipped.

16:14.080 --> 16:18.244
You're a sad, miserable human being.
And you want me to turn you. So here.

16:18.400 --> 16:20.164
Go ahead. Drink up.

16:20.320 --> 16:23.130
I'll kill you. You bite the mailman,
you'll be a vampire again.

16:23.280 --> 16:25.760
- Go ahead, come on.
- I can't, okay?

16:26.640 --> 16:28.483
No one's ever taken the cure before.

16:28.760 --> 16:32.048
If I die, there's a good chance
I may never wake up.

16:32.200 --> 16:34.248
And that would be tragic.

16:35.520 --> 16:40.048
And deep down in that mushy,
gushy, Elena-loving heart...

16:40.200 --> 16:44.603
there's a part of you
that doesn't want me to die.

16:44.760 --> 16:46.524
What are you doing here, Katherine?

16:46.880 --> 16:48.609
[PHONE RINGING]

16:52.160 --> 16:53.924
Salvatore residence.

16:54.080 --> 16:57.801
Hello, Principal Weber. This is Elena.

16:59.240 --> 17:01.049
Oh, dear.

17:02.280 --> 17:04.089
We'll find him.

17:06.200 --> 17:09.602
So Jeremy's been expelled.
Elena will be cool with that, right?

17:09.760 --> 17:13.445
- When I get back, you're gone.
- Damon, there's someone chasing me.

17:13.599 --> 17:16.683
- Then run. Run far away.
- Damon, you don't understand.

17:16.839 --> 17:18.365
I have enemies everywhere.

17:18.520 --> 17:22.205
What happens when word gets out
that I'm a human? I can't protect myself.

17:22.359 --> 17:24.521
I'm weak. And I'm slow.

17:24.680 --> 17:29.083
Do you have any idea what it's like
to run in heels? I have blisters, Damon.

17:29.240 --> 17:31.402
Please, just...

17:32.760 --> 17:34.603
Help me.

17:47.440 --> 17:48.521
STEFAN:
Elena.

18:03.320 --> 18:05.402
DAMON:
Wish I could say it gets better.

18:06.640 --> 18:09.644
STEFAN: The answer's no, Damon.
- Why?

18:10.000 --> 18:12.241
So you can keep dying,
coming back to life?

18:12.440 --> 18:15.728
You felt nothing but sheer agony
for three months.

18:15.880 --> 18:20.010
You hallucinate conversations with me
to have something to do.

18:22.320 --> 18:25.608
Just turn off that pesky humanity switch.

18:27.560 --> 18:30.962
- It won't take the pain away.
- Yeah, but it'll turn off your misery.

18:31.200 --> 18:35.205
- Your fear. Your hopelessness.
- And then what, huh?

18:35.360 --> 18:38.091
Say you actually notice I'm gone.
Say I get out of this.

18:38.240 --> 18:41.005
What good is it if I'm a monster again?

18:41.840 --> 18:44.241
How is that better than any of this?

18:58.120 --> 18:59.645
[CAROLINE SIGHS]

18:59.840 --> 19:04.129
Did you notice how Megan's juicer
takes up all the small-appliance space?

19:04.320 --> 19:07.449
She has an entire drawer dedicated
to organic linen.

19:07.600 --> 19:11.047
- What happened to privacy?
- Maybe if she didn't take long showers...

19:11.200 --> 19:13.328
I wouldn't have time
to go through her stuff.

19:13.480 --> 19:17.087
- How are you okay with a third roommate?
- We're trying to be functional.

19:17.240 --> 19:21.325
- Being functional means we need friends.
- We also need personal space.

19:21.480 --> 19:25.246
What if we suddenly get a craving
and I want to eat her?

19:25.400 --> 19:29.291
Or our blood bags go bad because
we can't store them in the mini fridge?

19:29.440 --> 19:32.330
And what the hell is protein water?

19:32.520 --> 19:36.047
You know what? Maybe if I drink it all,
she'll want to move out.

19:36.200 --> 19:37.611
Caroline, no...

19:37.800 --> 19:39.040
[COUGHING]

19:42.480 --> 19:43.970
Vervain.

19:44.160 --> 19:46.242
What's going on?

19:52.080 --> 19:54.287
Are you okay?

19:54.920 --> 19:56.410
Yeah, she's, uh, fine.

19:56.640 --> 19:58.165
MEGAN:
What happened?

19:58.320 --> 20:00.766
Water just went down the wrong pipe.

20:00.920 --> 20:03.082
I'm okay.
I shouldn't have touched your stuff.

20:03.240 --> 20:05.242
- I'm really sorry.
- It's fine.

20:05.400 --> 20:08.722
It just sounded like someone
was dying out here.

20:09.320 --> 20:11.561
Well, I'm glad you're okay.

20:17.520 --> 20:20.364
She knows who we are.
She drinks vervain water.

20:20.520 --> 20:22.568
- That doesn't mean she knows.
- Seriously?

20:22.720 --> 20:25.963
We share a bathroom with this girl.
What if she's a hunter...

20:26.160 --> 20:29.209
and she stakes us in the shower?
Or steals our daylight rings...

20:29.360 --> 20:31.886
and we burst into flames
when the sun comes up?

20:32.160 --> 20:34.162
If she was a hunter,
we'd be dead by now.

20:34.320 --> 20:37.642
I think we should lock her up,
let the vervain get out of her system...

20:37.920 --> 20:39.649
and then we compel her to forget us.

20:39.840 --> 20:42.446
Caroline,
I'm not kidnapping our roommate.

20:42.600 --> 20:46.047
The best way to convince her
that we're normal is to act normal.

20:46.200 --> 20:49.807
And do normal, human, freshman-y stuff.

20:49.960 --> 20:51.291
Such as?

20:54.680 --> 20:56.284
[UPBEAT POP MUSIC
PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

20:56.480 --> 20:58.369
[CHATTERING AND LAUGHING]

21:00.240 --> 21:02.811
JESSE:
Hey, I remember you.

21:03.320 --> 21:05.527
Hey. Flyer guy.

21:05.680 --> 21:07.409
Jesse, technically.

21:07.560 --> 21:09.369
But "flyer guy" works too.

21:09.520 --> 21:12.330
I'm Elena. This is, uh, Caroline.

21:12.480 --> 21:14.562
- Nice to meet you.
- Hi.

21:19.120 --> 21:21.691
ELENA: You can't be nice to the guy?
- I'm with Tyler.

21:21.880 --> 21:23.803
Are you? Because he hasn't called.

21:23.960 --> 21:25.610
From the mountains of Appalachia?

21:25.800 --> 21:28.485
I don't want you to get your hopes up
thinking he's coming...

21:28.680 --> 21:30.250
when he hasn't shown interest.

21:30.400 --> 21:33.370
Did you tell Damon
you were having dreams about Stefan?

21:34.360 --> 21:37.091
See? No relationship is perfect.

21:37.240 --> 21:38.321
[THUD]

21:38.520 --> 21:39.851
What the hell?

21:40.120 --> 21:43.090
Someone must own this place.
We have to be invited in.

21:43.280 --> 21:45.965
Hey, I was wondering
if you guys were gonna make it.

21:46.160 --> 21:48.447
You going in, or...?

21:48.920 --> 21:50.046
Go ahead.

21:53.280 --> 21:54.770
Why are you just standing there?

21:54.920 --> 21:57.048
We were just...

21:57.200 --> 21:58.929
Caroline?

21:59.080 --> 22:01.651
- Waiting for someone.
ELENA: She's late. Heh.

22:02.360 --> 22:03.600
- So...
- Yeah.

22:03.800 --> 22:06.371
Right, well, I'm gonna go hang.

22:06.520 --> 22:08.045
CAROLINE:
Okay.

22:09.760 --> 22:12.889
Like I said, she knows.

22:13.360 --> 22:15.010
DAMON:
One day.

22:15.160 --> 22:18.562
- One day where you don't screw it up.
- Leave me alone, Damon.

22:18.720 --> 22:21.121
You're lucky you didn't
put one of those idiots in I.C.U.

22:21.280 --> 22:23.089
Says the guy that once killed me.

22:23.240 --> 22:27.006
Yes, in the privacy of your own home,
away from prying eyes.

22:27.160 --> 22:30.243
Unlike you, who went all hunter
in the middle of a hallway.

22:30.400 --> 22:32.164
You got expelled, genius.

22:32.800 --> 22:34.609
That mean I don't have to go back
to school?

22:34.760 --> 22:37.764
I compelled Principal Weber
into a generous three-day suspension.

22:38.240 --> 22:41.323
Elena does not need to know about this.

22:41.800 --> 22:44.610
Finish eating. Meet me outside.

22:48.400 --> 22:51.324
- Hello, Damon.
- Stefan.

22:52.040 --> 22:53.280
Welcome home.

22:53.440 --> 22:55.249
Thanks.

23:04.120 --> 23:05.929
Hey, Megan, it's Elena.

23:06.200 --> 23:10.285
I'm just calling to let you know why we left,
so call me when you get a chance. Bye.

23:10.480 --> 23:14.530
Ugh, okay. It's settled.
When she leaves, we grab her.

23:14.720 --> 23:18.088
Or we could just let her know
that you weren't feeling well.

23:18.320 --> 23:22.166
She saw us stuck at the threshold. We
might as well have flashed her our fangs.

23:22.320 --> 23:24.926
There's no way that
out of the thousands of freshmen...

23:25.080 --> 23:28.368
we were randomly paired
with someone who knows about vampires.

23:28.520 --> 23:30.170
Maybe it wasn't random.

23:30.320 --> 23:31.367
[CELL PHONE RINGS]

23:31.520 --> 23:33.363
Megan's calling. Hey, Megan.

23:33.520 --> 23:36.126
MEGAN [WHIMPERING]:
Elena, you have to <i>help</i> me.

23:36.280 --> 23:37.486
<i>He's chasing me.</i>

23:37.680 --> 23:39.887
- Megan, who's chasing you?
MEGAN: <i>Help</i> me!

23:40.040 --> 23:41.121
[WINDOW RATTLING]

23:41.280 --> 23:42.327
<i>Oh, my God.</i>

23:42.520 --> 23:45.967
We can't come inside.
The line's too long.

23:46.240 --> 23:49.130
<i>- If you come out...</i> Where <i>are you?
MEGAN: Elena, please help me!</i>

23:49.320 --> 23:51.800
Megan? Can you hear me?
Just get outside and we can help you.

23:51.960 --> 23:53.644
[MEGAN SCREAMS]
[CAROLINE & ELENA SHRIEK]

23:53.800 --> 23:55.245
Oh, my God.

23:55.400 --> 23:56.640
[ELENA GASPS]

24:02.440 --> 24:05.011
CAROLINE:
Who did this to her?

24:07.920 --> 24:09.684
This was a vampire.

24:12.280 --> 24:17.366
Look, I get why you haven't called me back
all summer. I wouldn't call me back either.

24:17.520 --> 24:19.682
You mean because
you stole my girlfriend?

24:20.760 --> 24:22.410
I'm over it.

24:23.040 --> 24:24.326
Cheers.

24:30.160 --> 24:32.083
Katherine's living at Chateau Salvatore.

24:32.960 --> 24:35.964
- How do you know that?
- Because I can read your mind.

24:37.480 --> 24:38.686
[CHUCKLES]

24:38.880 --> 24:40.325
Kidding, buddy.

24:40.480 --> 24:43.324
Katherine called me first. Remember?

24:43.480 --> 24:46.927
- It's always been me first.
- Right.

24:51.400 --> 24:53.926
SILAS:
Hey, Jeremy. Looking good, man.

24:55.480 --> 24:57.130
Hey, Stefan. Glad you're back.

24:57.560 --> 24:58.925
Yeah.

24:59.160 --> 25:00.844
Yeah.

25:01.000 --> 25:04.607
- All right, I'll, uh, see you at home.
- Great.

25:07.000 --> 25:10.721
Something's wrong. When he touched me
I felt a chill where my tattoo was.

25:10.880 --> 25:12.325
What are you talking about?

25:12.480 --> 25:15.404
Right before I died,
Silas grabbed me and I felt the same thing.

25:15.560 --> 25:19.167
Silas is gone. Bonnie turned him
into a big piece of rock, remember?

25:19.320 --> 25:22.802
I died. Jeremy,
I bound the magic that took down Silas.

25:22.960 --> 25:25.850
When I died, the spell must have broken.
He's free.

25:26.040 --> 25:29.567
- That was Silas.
- That's impossible.

25:32.520 --> 25:33.851
I'm a hunter.

25:34.000 --> 25:37.004
Our whole reason for existing
is to kill him.

25:38.560 --> 25:41.564
I know what I'm feeling, Damon.
That was Silas.

25:41.720 --> 25:44.405
I watched him walk
through a crowd of people that saw Stefan.

25:44.600 --> 25:47.206
There's no way he could fool
that many people at once.

25:47.480 --> 25:50.086
He's psychic, but no one's that psychic.

25:50.240 --> 25:52.163
What did he want?

25:58.320 --> 25:59.731
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

26:04.520 --> 26:09.003
Why are you in my brother's bathtub?

26:09.160 --> 26:11.083
Why aren't you?

26:12.840 --> 26:16.367
I will say that's a tempting offer.

26:16.520 --> 26:18.682
Ooh. He flirts.

26:19.760 --> 26:21.762
I like Elena-less Stefan.

26:21.920 --> 26:28.724
You know, human looks better on you
than I would've guessed, Katherine.

26:29.040 --> 26:31.611
I think you just accidentally
gave me a compliment.

26:31.760 --> 26:37.403
No, I mean it. You sitting here
all weak and vulnerable.

26:38.520 --> 26:40.522
It works.

26:50.560 --> 26:51.925
- Time for a field trip.
- Unh!

27:07.440 --> 27:09.044
[GASPS]

27:09.200 --> 27:12.522
Get her out of here.
Don't tell me where you're going.

27:13.680 --> 27:16.570
God, you're slow.
Guess vamp speed came with the upgrade.

27:16.720 --> 27:20.520
- Get out of my way and give me Katherine.
- First drop the Stefan look.

27:20.680 --> 27:22.011
[CHUCKLES]

27:22.800 --> 27:24.006
What?

27:25.480 --> 27:27.244
[SIREN WAILING]

27:28.480 --> 27:30.562
ELENA:
What is happening?

27:30.720 --> 27:33.769
Our roommate is dead.
There was a vampire at the party.

27:33.960 --> 27:35.928
We don't know what she knew
or who she told.

27:36.080 --> 27:37.445
We should get out of here.

27:38.840 --> 27:42.083
Caroline,
I left that message in her voice mail.

27:42.280 --> 27:43.884
Don't worry, I took her phone.

27:44.360 --> 27:46.124
- You what?
DIANE: Hey, girls.

27:47.000 --> 27:50.288
I'm Diane Freeman,
head of campus security. Are you okay?

27:51.120 --> 27:53.248
I mean, I think so.

27:53.440 --> 27:55.044
I understand Megan was your roommate.

27:55.240 --> 27:58.449
- I'm so sorry you had to find her like this.
- Do they know what happened?

27:58.600 --> 28:02.605
We found a note. Apparently,
she was struggling with severe depression.

28:02.760 --> 28:05.001
Wait, what do you mean,
you found a note?

28:05.200 --> 28:06.770
Your roommate took her own life.

28:07.720 --> 28:09.404
You think this was a suicide?

28:09.560 --> 28:11.324
DIANE:
We're convinced it was a suicide.

28:11.480 --> 28:14.768
But we can't seem to find her cell phone.
Have you seen it?

28:16.000 --> 28:17.525
- No.
- Okay.

28:17.680 --> 28:19.284
If it turns up, let us know?

28:23.520 --> 28:25.045
What is going on?

28:26.320 --> 28:28.607
DAMON: If I hear the word doppelganger
one more time...

28:28.760 --> 28:31.843
I think I'm gonna actually have to learn
how to spell it.

28:32.000 --> 28:35.721
You say you don't believe me, and yet
your mind is spinning at the possibility.

28:35.880 --> 28:37.769
A, get out of my head.

28:37.920 --> 28:40.810
B, I think I'd know if my little brother
had an evil twin.

28:41.280 --> 28:42.691
Oh, we're not twins.

28:42.840 --> 28:44.922
See, when I became truly immortal...

28:45.080 --> 28:49.404
nature retaliated by creating
a version of me that was killable.

28:49.560 --> 28:50.721
It's called a shadow self.

28:50.880 --> 28:54.009
Well, whatever you are,
your plan didn't work. Cure's gone.

28:54.160 --> 28:56.561
Now, what do you want with Katherine?

28:57.640 --> 29:01.565
I could tell you, but wouldn't it be so
much more fun if it were a surprise?

29:02.640 --> 29:05.928
- You're not getting her.
- How well do you know your brother?

29:06.080 --> 29:09.527
Do you think he would leave
for three months without a phone call...

29:09.720 --> 29:12.371
so you could live happily ever after
with the love of his life?

29:13.080 --> 29:16.323
Or did you just delude yourself
into thinking it would be that easy?

29:20.600 --> 29:23.843
- Where' <i>s</i> Stefan?
- He's suffering. Like I suffered.

29:24.320 --> 29:27.847
So call the hunter, bring me Katherine...

29:28.000 --> 29:31.686
and then I will tell you
where your little brother is.

29:38.880 --> 29:40.644
Where are we going?

29:44.880 --> 29:47.167
Are you deaf? I said, where are we going?

29:47.360 --> 29:49.010
[CELL PHONE RINGS]

29:51.640 --> 29:54.086
- Hey.
- How far did you get?

29:54.240 --> 29:57.164
JEREMY: You <i>said</i> not to <i>tell you.</i>
- You pick now to listen to me?

29:58.600 --> 30:03.083
- We just passed Old Miller Road.
- Good. Turn around. Bring her back.

30:03.840 --> 30:05.524
What? No.

30:17.120 --> 30:20.090
What are you doing? Stop.
You can't take me back there.

30:20.240 --> 30:22.891
Damon wouldn't hand me over.
Silas got in his head.

30:23.040 --> 30:24.690
Shut up, Katherine.

30:30.480 --> 30:31.720
Hey, what the hell?

30:31.880 --> 30:33.370
[TIRES SCREECHING]

30:43.800 --> 30:45.404
SILAS:
Hmm.

30:46.640 --> 30:49.769
Ooh. Your thoughts are churning.

30:50.320 --> 30:52.687
It's like a spool of pink taffy.

30:53.680 --> 30:55.728
It's very messy, but very fun to watch.

30:55.920 --> 30:58.605
- Anyone ever tell you that's creepy?
- You're worried.

30:58.840 --> 31:00.763
"Jeremy's not answering the phone."

31:00.960 --> 31:02.530
"They should be back by now."

31:03.680 --> 31:06.126
You think something's very wrong.

31:09.400 --> 31:12.085
- Here you go, mayor. On the house.
- Thank you, Matt.

31:12.320 --> 31:15.642
So, uh, when's Bonnie coming back?

31:15.800 --> 31:17.370
You know, I'm not sure.

31:17.560 --> 31:20.848
But, um, if you talk to her,
tell her I said hi, okay?

31:21.000 --> 31:22.684
- Yeah.
- Thanks for the beer.

31:22.840 --> 31:24.444
You're welcome.

31:36.280 --> 31:37.441
No way.

31:46.760 --> 31:48.808
Nadia?

31:52.040 --> 31:53.201
You remember me.

31:53.360 --> 31:56.364
Yeah, I remember you.

31:58.240 --> 32:00.242
You got Rebekah and me drunk
and robbed us.

32:00.400 --> 32:03.529
But it was fun until then, no?

32:05.040 --> 32:06.804
How did you know how to find me?

32:07.480 --> 32:09.801
Let's skip the how and get to the why.

32:14.280 --> 32:16.248
This wasn't mine to take.

32:16.920 --> 32:19.207
You traveled 4000 miles
to give me back a ring?

32:19.360 --> 32:23.251
- Hey, if you don't want it...
- No, I want it.

32:34.800 --> 32:37.041
Looks better on you anyway.

32:39.000 --> 32:40.411
[MATT GASPS]

32:42.800 --> 32:44.131
[SPEAKING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

32:52.480 --> 32:54.448
ELENA [ON RECORDING]:
Hey, Megan, <i>it's Elena.</i>

32:54.600 --> 32:57.444
<i>- I'm just calling to let you know...
- Delete.</i>

33:07.440 --> 33:09.966
Someone's been in here.

33:15.320 --> 33:16.526
Megan's tablet's gone.

33:16.720 --> 33:18.961
Along with her so-called suicide note?

33:20.320 --> 33:21.845
Can I see the phone for a second?

33:22.080 --> 33:24.048
It just doesn't make any sense.

33:24.200 --> 33:27.966
First, the roommate we're not supposed
to have might know about vampires...

33:28.240 --> 33:30.368
and then happens to be killed
by a vampire.

33:30.520 --> 33:32.887
And now the school's covering it up?

33:33.040 --> 33:36.044
Seriously, who is this girl?

33:36.240 --> 33:39.483
Whatever's going on,
it's not just about our roommate.

33:39.920 --> 33:42.048
It's about me.

33:43.160 --> 33:44.730
That's Megan.

33:48.000 --> 33:49.525
With my dad.

33:53.120 --> 33:54.884
[ENGINE HISSING]

33:57.880 --> 33:59.245
JEREMY:
Hey.

34:00.120 --> 34:01.167
[GROANING]

34:01.360 --> 34:02.600
Please.

34:12.040 --> 34:13.565
[GASPING]

34:16.000 --> 34:17.445
[GROANS]

34:23.120 --> 34:25.407
Jeremy, hold on.

34:25.560 --> 34:27.960
Hey, I know you can hear me.

34:28.360 --> 34:29.929
Jeremy.

34:35.480 --> 34:38.449
Jeremy. Aah!

34:38.800 --> 34:41.804
Open your eyes, Jer.
You do not get to die on me, you hear me?

34:41.960 --> 34:44.690
I'm supposed to be taking care of you,
you little punk.

34:45.679 --> 34:48.047
Wake up or I'll kill you myself.

34:51.960 --> 34:53.199
[GROANS]

34:57.000 --> 35:00.083
Unh. Katherine is gone.

35:04.600 --> 35:06.364
I don't care.

35:07.880 --> 35:09.370
TYLER [ON RECORDING]:
Hey, Caroline.

35:09.520 --> 35:15.482
<i>Look, I've put a lot of thought into this
and decided to defer school for now.</i>

35:15.640 --> 35:20.407
<i>This werewolf pack I'm helping,
they need me.</i>

35:20.560 --> 35:22.688
<i>I know it's lame to do this
over the phone...</i>

35:22.840 --> 35:25.161
<i>but I figure this way
it's harder for you to kill me.</i>

35:25.320 --> 35:27.004
[CAROLINE SOBBING]

35:27.160 --> 35:30.687
<i>I'm really, really sorry, Care.</i>

35:31.840 --> 35:33.922
<i>But this is important.</i>

35:45.320 --> 35:46.810
[SOBBING CONTINUES]

35:52.840 --> 35:54.001
You Okay?

35:56.640 --> 35:58.005
Yeah.

35:58.400 --> 36:00.641
Yeah, I'm fine.

36:06.680 --> 36:08.409
I'm sorry, Caroline.

36:13.000 --> 36:15.241
I'm really glad that you're here.

36:16.040 --> 36:19.089
I'm really glad you're here too.

36:52.200 --> 36:54.441
DAMON:
You're thinking about it.

36:56.240 --> 36:58.288
Flip the switch, brother.

36:58.840 --> 37:01.446
Put yourself out of this misery. Please.

37:04.400 --> 37:07.404
Did you forget how long it took me
to come back last time?

37:08.520 --> 37:10.204
Everything I lost in the process?

37:10.360 --> 37:12.681
You don't deserve this, Stefan.

37:12.840 --> 37:15.161
You did the right thing, you walked away.

37:16.760 --> 37:18.091
You let us be happy.

37:18.240 --> 37:20.004
This is what you get in return?

37:20.160 --> 37:22.162
How is that fair?

37:24.080 --> 37:25.366
<i>Hey-</i>

37:29.080 --> 37:31.287
Just turn it off.

37:34.480 --> 37:35.925
Turn it off.

37:42.320 --> 37:45.085
Wait. Stay with me, Stefan.

37:49.760 --> 37:51.330
What are you doing here?

37:51.800 --> 37:55.725
I know this is torture, but stay with me.

37:56.680 --> 38:02.210
Your humanity is the one thing
that makes you who you are.

38:02.360 --> 38:04.362
Don't let go.

38:05.720 --> 38:06.960
Please, Stefan.

38:10.200 --> 38:12.328
For me.

38:22.000 --> 38:25.721
Hey, sorry it took so long
to call you back.

38:25.960 --> 38:28.440
- Car trouble.
- What happened?

38:29.280 --> 38:32.250
Ah, some idiot broke the window.

38:32.400 --> 38:36.007
Based on your voice mail, sounds like
your day sucked worse than mine.

38:36.160 --> 38:39.164
- You all right? Do you wanna come home?
- I can't.

38:40.440 --> 38:44.490
And especially if my dad's connected
to this somehow, I need to know why.

38:44.640 --> 38:46.324
Yeah, it's probably for the best.

38:46.480 --> 38:49.245
<i>It'll give me more bonding time
with your brother.</i>

38:49.800 --> 38:51.290
I love you, Damon.

38:53.160 --> 38:54.605
Good night.

38:57.520 --> 38:58.567
[SIGHS]

38:58.760 --> 39:00.285
You didn't tell her Silas was here.

39:00.560 --> 39:04.531
Nor did I tell her Stefan's missing,
Katherine's in town or you got expelled.

39:04.680 --> 39:07.570
- So you lied.
- No, I withheld a bit of the truth...

39:07.720 --> 39:11.566
so that Elena wouldn't drop everything
and come running home to help.

39:11.720 --> 39:13.006
[SIGHS]

39:13.680 --> 39:16.081
I'll figure all this out.

39:17.280 --> 39:19.442
I hope everyone enjoyed the party.

39:19.600 --> 39:22.285
[CHEERING AND CLAPPING]

39:22.440 --> 39:27.480
It is truly great
to have an end-of-summer tradition.

39:28.320 --> 39:31.529
My daughter has her own
end-of-summer tradition...

39:31.720 --> 39:34.007
of over-indulging in the cotton candy.

39:34.160 --> 39:35.207
[ALL CHUCKLE]

39:35.360 --> 39:37.283
Now she's off traveling the world...

39:37.440 --> 39:40.922
and sending her old man postcards
from all her great adventures.

39:41.080 --> 39:42.127
[BONNIE CHUCKLES]

39:42.320 --> 39:45.961
Family is one of our core values
here in Mystic Falls.

39:46.440 --> 39:49.330
It's what this block party celebrates.

39:49.480 --> 39:51.687
Family as a community.

39:51.840 --> 39:52.921
Stefan?

39:53.080 --> 39:54.923
Do you mind if I say a few words?

39:55.120 --> 39:58.203
- Maybe when we're done here, okay?
<i>- I'll</i> take it from here, mayor.

40:02.400 --> 40:04.004
Oh, my God.

40:04.200 --> 40:05.884
[AUDIENCE MURMURING]
[SILAS CLEARS THROAT]

40:06.040 --> 40:08.008
You're probably wondering how
I did that.

40:08.400 --> 40:10.641
It's pretty basic mind control.

40:10.840 --> 40:14.367
And until now, it's been fairly limited
to one person at a time.

40:16.160 --> 40:21.041
But this summer, I've consumed
an immeasurable amount of blood.

40:21.200 --> 40:22.690
[AUDIENCE CHATTERING]

40:23.200 --> 40:27.046
And I've felt myself getting stronger
and stronger every day.

40:27.200 --> 40:31.046
And I started to wonder,
what are the limits to my powers?

40:31.240 --> 40:32.651
How many people can I influence?

40:32.880 --> 40:34.484
Two? Ten?

40:35.680 --> 40:36.966
An entire town square?

40:37.160 --> 40:38.571
[CHATTERING INTENSIFIES]

40:38.720 --> 40:41.121
Everyone stop talking.

40:41.280 --> 40:43.089
[CHATTERING STOPS]

